{"id":8452,"date":"2025-09-22T07:40:03","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T07:40:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8452"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:32:46","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:32:46","slug":"jabalpur-pachmarhi-bhopal-indore","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/jabalpur-pachmarhi-bhopal-indore\/","title":{"rendered":"JABALPUR PACHMARHI BHOPAL INDORE"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8542,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[94],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8452","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-heart-of-india-madhyapradesh","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8453],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8452","price":29777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":9,"nights":8,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Heart of India Madhya Pradesh: Jabalpur \u2013 Pachmarhi \u2013 Bhopal \u2013 Indore (8N\/9D)<\/strong><br>Discover the soul of India with this enriching journey through Madhya Pradesh, the country\u2019s heartland of culture, history, and nature. Begin in <strong>Jabalpur<\/strong>, famous for the breathtaking <strong>Marble Rocks at Bhedaghat<\/strong> and the roaring <strong>Dhuandhar Falls<\/strong>. Move on to the hill station of <strong>Pachmarhi<\/strong>, a serene retreat with lush greenery, waterfalls, caves, and colonial charm. Continue to <strong>Bhopal<\/strong>, the city of lakes, where modern elegance blends with heritage, offering visits to the <strong>Sanchi Stupa<\/strong>, museums, and vibrant bazaars. Conclude your journey in <strong>Indore<\/strong>, a bustling city known for its royal palaces, street food culture, and spiritual sites like Omkareshwar and Maheshwar nearby. This 8N\/9D itinerary offers a perfect blend of nature, history, spirituality, and urban flavor, making Madhya Pradesh truly the <em>Heart of India<\/em>.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":" 3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n Breakfast, Dinner, Lunch\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":"Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"3. What are the major highlights of this tour? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jabalpur: Bhedaghat Marble Rocks, Dhuandhar Falls, Madan Mahal Fort Pachmarhi: Bee Falls, Pandava Caves, Dhupgarh, Jata Shankar Caves Bhopal: Upper &amp; Lower Lakes, Sanchi Stupa, Tribal Museum Indore: Rajwada Palace, Lal Bagh Palace, Sarafa Bazaar (street food), nearby Omkareshwar &amp; Maheshwar<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. Is Pachmarhi suitable for senior citizens and kids? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, Pachmarhi is a calm hill station, but some spots require short treks\/walks. Vehicles are restricted in the core area, so local gypsy rides are arranged.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":900,"height":596,"file":"2025\/09\/43.png","filesize":1008211,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"43-300x199.png","width":300,"height":199,"filesize":63623,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-300x199.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"43-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":29162,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-150x150.png"},"medium_large":{"file":"43-768x509.png","width":768,"height":509,"filesize":361330,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-768x509.png"},"trip-thumb-size":{"file":"43-374x226.png","width":374,"height":226,"filesize":87394,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-374x226.png"},"destination-thumb-size":{"file":"43-600x596.png","width":600,"height":596,"filesize":435666,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-600x596.png"},"destination-thumb-trip-size":{"file":"43-410x250.png","width":410,"height":250,"filesize":103927,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-410x250.png"},"activities-thumb-size":{"file":"43-600x596.png","width":600,"height":596,"filesize":435666,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/43-600x596.png"},"trip-single-size":{"file":"43-900x490.png","width":900,"height":490,"filesize":498755,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"http